# This document lists all backend `.env` variables, their purpose, default values, what breaks if they're missing, and how to test them.
# Backend ENV Sheet

# | Layer   | ENV Variable                          | Mandatory / Optional  | Default Value                    | Description                                          | What breaks when missing / invalid                                      | How to Test Step‑by‑Step |
# |---------|---------------------------------------|----------------------|-----------------------------------|------------------------------------------------------|-------------------------------------------------------------------------|---------------------------|
# | BACKEND | **OPENAI_API_KEY**                    | Mandatory            | *(none)*                          | OpenAI key to use OpenAI LLMs                       | LLM calls fail (chat/extraction), 401 errors                            | Set invalid key → call `/chat` → expect failure → set valid key |
# | BACKEND | **DIFFBOT_API_KEY**                   | Mandatory            | *(none)*                          | API key for Diffbot extraction                      | Selecting Diffbot model fails; extraction errors                        | Choose Diffbot model → run extraction → expect failure → fix key |
# | BACKEND | **BUCKET**                            | Mandatory            | *(none)*                          | GCS bucket to store uploads                          | File uploads fail; “No bucket configured” in logs                       | Upload file → fails → configure bucket |
# | BACKEND | **DUPLICATE_TEXT_DISTANCE**           | Mandatory            | `5`                               | Distance threshold for duplicate detection           | Post‑processing fails or dedup inaccurate                               | Generate graph → inspect logs → adjust value |
# | BACKEND | **DUPLICATE_SCORE_VALUE**             | Mandatory            | `0.97`                            | Score threshold for duplicate nodes                  | Duplicate matching too strict/loose                                     | Generate graph → inspect duplicate behavior |
# | BACKEND | **EFFECTIVE_SEARCH_RATIO**            | Mandatory            | `1`                               | Search effectiveness tuning                          | Search/QA degraded                                                      | Run QA → compare results |
# | BACKEND | **NEO4J_URI**                         | Optional             | `neo4j://database:7687`           | Neo4j connection URI (use `neo4j+s` for Aura)        | Cannot connect to Neo4j                                                | Set wrong host → call `/docs` → fix |
# | BACKEND | **NEO4J_USERNAME**                    | Optional             | `neo4j`                           | Neo4j username                                       | Auth failure                                                            | Set wrong user → observe error |
# | BACKEND | **NEO4J_PASSWORD**                    | Optional             | `password`                        | Neo4j password                                       | Auth failure                                                            | Set wrong password → observe error |
# | BACKEND | **NEO4J_DATABASE**                    | Optional             | `neo4j`                           | Target database name                                 | Unknown database errors                                                 | Set non-existing DB → run query |
# | BACKEND | **EMBEDDING_MODEL**                   | Optional             | `all-MiniLM-L6-v2`                | Embedding model                                      | Falls back to default                                                  | Clear value → run embedding |
# | BACKEND | **IS_EMBEDDING**                      | Optional             | `TRUE`                            | Enable/disable embeddings                             | Vector/KNN features unavailable                                         | Set false → test KNN |
# | BACKEND | **KNN_MIN_SCORE**                     | Optional             | `0.94`                            | Minimum KNN score                                    | Lower/higher recall                                                     | Adjust → run QA |
# | BACKEND | **GEMINI_ENABLED**                    | Optional             | `FALSE`                           | Enable Gemini models                                 | Gemini models not available                                             | Toggle → check model dropdown |
# | BACKEND | **GCP_LOG_METRICS_ENABLED**           | Optional             | `FALSE`                           | Enable GCP metrics logging                           | No functional effect; only logs                                         | Toggle → check logs |
# | BACKEND | **NUMBER_OF_CHUNKS_TO_COMBINE**       | Optional             | `5`                               | Chunks combined during embedding                     | Processing speed changes                                                 | Modify → process document |
# | BACKEND | **UPDATE_GRAPH_CHUNKS_PROCESSED**     | Optional             | `20`                              | Progress update interval                             | Progress bar granularity changes                                        | Adjust → observe |
# | BACKEND | **LANGCHAIN_API_KEY**                 | Optional             | *(none)*                          | LangChain API key                                    | LangChain tracing disabled                                              | Enable key → check traces |
# | BACKEND | **LANGCHAIN_PROJECT**                 | Optional             | *(none)*                          | LangChain project name                               | No project grouping in traces                                           | Set project → verify traces |
# | BACKEND | **LANGCHAIN_TRACING_V2**              | Optional             | `TRUE`                            | Enable LangChain tracing v2                          | No tracing if disabled                                                  | Toggle → observe |
# | BACKEND | **LANGCHAIN_ENDPOINT**                | Optional             | `https://api.smith.langchain.com` | LangChain endpoint                                   | Tracing fails if wrong URL                                              | Set invalid → observe errors |
# | BACKEND | **GCS_FILE_CACHE**                    | Optional             | `FALSE`                           | Cache files in GCS instead of local                  | —                                                                       | Toggle → check file locations |
# | BACKEND | **ENTITY_EMBEDDING**                  | Optional             | `FALSE`                           | Enable entity‑level embeddings                       | Missing entity vectors if disabled                                      | Enable → process → verify vectors |
# | BACKEND | **LLM_MODEL_CONFIG_ollama_<model>**   | Optional             | *(none)*                          | Local Ollama model config (`name,url`)               | Cannot use local LLM                                                    | Set config → choose model |
# | BACKEND | **RAGAS_EMBEDDING_MODEL**             | Optional             | `openai`                          | Embedding model for RAGAS eval                       | RAGAS eval fails or defaults                                            | Unset → run eval → set openai |
# | BACKEND | **YOUTUBE_TRANSCRIPT_PROXY**          | Optional             | *(none)*                          | Proxy for YouTube transcripts                        | YouTube extraction fails in restricted networks                         | Test YouTube → set proxy |
# | BACKEND | **GRAPH_CLEANUP_MODEL**               | Optional             | `0.97`                            | Cleanup model/parameter                              | Cleanup step inconsistent                                               | Set invalid → observe |
# | BACKEND | **MAX_TOKEN_CHUNK_SIZE**              | Optional             | `10000`                           | Max tokens per chunk                                 | Large docs error if too small                                           | Lower → process large file |


# Frontend Environment Variables
# This document lists all frontend `.env` variables, their purpose, default values, what breaks if they're missing, and how to test them.

# | Layer    | ENV Variable               | Mandatory / Optional                 | Default Value                                                                                                                                          | Description                            | What breaks when missing / invalid                      | How to Test Step‑by‑Step |
# |----------|----------------------------|--------------------------------------|--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|----------------------------------------|---------------------------------------------------------|---------------------------|
# | FRONTEND | **VITE_BLOOM_URL**         | Mandatory                            | https://workspace-preview.neo4j.io/workspace/explore?connectURL={CONNECT_URL}&search=Show+me+a+graph&featureGenAISuggestions=true&featureGenAISuggestionsInternal=true | Bloom visualization URL| Bloom button fails or opens wrong page                  | Clear value → click "Open in Bloom" → expect failure → restore |
# | FRONTEND | **VITE_REACT_APP_SOURCES** | Mandatory                            | local,youtube,wiki,s3                                                                                                                                  | Enabled input sources                  | Upload source dropdown empty/crashes                    | Remove → reload upload page |
# | FRONTEND | **VITE_CHAT_MODES**        | Mandatory                            | vector,graph+vector,graph,hybrid                                                                                                                       | Available chat modes                   | Chat mode selector empty / fails                        | Remove → open chat → expect error |
# | FRONTEND | **VITE_ENV**               | Mandatory                            | DEV or PROD                                                                                                                                            | Environment selection                  | App fails to boot or shows blank                        | Unset → reload → expect blank screen |
# | FRONTEND | **VITE_LLM_MODELS**        | Mandatory                            | diffbot,openai_gpt_3.5,openai_gpt_4o,openai_gpt_4o_mini,gemini_1.5_pro,gemini_1.5_flash,azure_ai_gpt_35,azure_ai_gpt_4o,ollama_llama3,groq_llama3_70b,anthropic_claude_3_5_sonnet| Supported LLM models list| LLM model dropdown empty; features disabled | Unset → open model selector |
# | FRONTEND | **VITE_BACKEND_API_URL**   | Optional                             | http://localhost:8000                                                                                                                                  | Backend API base URL                   | All API calls fail; uploads/chat broken                 | Remove → try upload/chat |
# | FRONTEND | **VITE_TIME_PER_PAGE**     | Optional                             | 50                                                                                                                                                     | Time per page for processing           | Only timing differences                                 | Modify → process doc |
# | FRONTEND | **VITE_CHUNK_SIZE**        | Optional                             | 5242880                                                                                                                                                | Upload chunk size (bytes)              | Large file upload may fail if too small                 | Lower → upload large file |
# | FRONTEND | **VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID**  | Optional                             | *(empty)*                                                                                                                                              | Google OAuth client ID                 | Google login unavailable                                | Try Google login |
# | FRONTEND | **VITE_LLM_MODELS_PROD**   | Optional                             | openai_gpt_4o,openai_gpt_4o_mini,diffbot,gemini_1.5_flash                                                                                              | Models shown in PROD environment       | Wrong/limited model list                                | Switch VITE_ENV=PROD → remove value → check dropdown |
